  "texts": [
    "Dialect recording quality is also one of the critical elements in corpus construction.",
    "Using professional microphones to directly collect dialect sounds in a quiet indoor environment can reduce noise interference and avoid problems such as distortion.",
    "The high sample rate, along with a high bit depth and multiple channels, will ensure the better audio quality of speech recordings, and vice versa (Rabiner and Juang 1993).",
    "The 16 kHz sampling rate with 16-bit depth is a common choice.",
    "For example, Li and Zhao (2017) recorded the Hengyang dialect corpus in such condition, the RASC863 corpus, etc."
  ],
